---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const inquiryHref = 'https://circularaction.org/ca-reimbursements';
---

<BaseLayout title="SB 54 in California" description="A starting point for what's ahead under SB 54 and how to get involved.">
  <div class="caa-sb54-landing">
    <section class="caa-sb54-landing__hero">
      <p class="caa-sb54-landing__eyebrow">Welcome</p>
      <h1>This is your starting point for what's ahead under <em>SB&nbsp;54</em> and how you can get involved.</h1>
      <p class="caa-sb54-landing__lede">
        California's recycling, composting and reuse system is evolving. Starting now and in the coming years, SB&nbsp;54 will be driving real improvements in how single-use packaging and food serviceware is collected, processed, and recycled or returned for use – creating a more consistent, connected system statewide.
      </p>
      <p class="caa-sb54-landing__lede">
        Whether you've already connected with CAA or are learning about CAA for the first time, this page is designed to help you understand what's coming next and how you can engage.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="caa-sb54-landing__card">
      <h2>Get Started</h2>
      <p>CAA is connecting with local interest holders across the system:</p>
      <dl class="caa-sb54-landing__stages">
        <div class="caa-sb54-landing__stage">
          <dt class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-label">Local &amp; community</dt>
          <dd class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-providers">Local Jurisdictions, Tribes, Community-Based Organizations</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="caa-sb54-landing__stage">
          <dt class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-label">Collection</dt>
          <dd class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-providers">Haulers, Alternative Collection Providers</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="caa-sb54-landing__stage">
          <dt class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-label">Sort &amp; process</dt>
          <dd class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-providers">Transfer Stations, MRFs, Compost Facilities</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="caa-sb54-landing__stage">
          <dt class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-label">End markets &amp; reuse</dt>
          <dd class="caa-sb54-landing__stage-providers">End Markets, Reuse Programs</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
      <p>
        Outreach is ongoing, but you don't have to wait to get involved. If you want to explore funding opportunities or next steps, connect with CAA.
      </p>
      <div class="sqs-block-button-container--left">
        <a href={inquiryHref} class="sqs-block-button-element sqs-block-button-element--medium sqs-button-element--primary">Get in touch</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <aside class="caa-sb54-landing__note">
      <h2>Learn More</h2>
      <p>More information is coming soon to this site.</p>
    </aside>

    {/* When FAQs are ready, the "Learn More" aside above replaces with:
        <h2>Learn More</h2>
        <p>Want a clearer view of what's ahead?</p>
        <a href="/faqs">Explore what's coming (FAQs)</a>
        Source: Dana copy revisions 2026-05-12. */}
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /*
   * Scoped under .caa-sb54-landing so this CSS does not leak into the rest of
   * the Squarespace page when pasted into a Code Block. Only layout primitives
   * are kept; typography, colors, and button styling fall through to the
   * Squarespace site's design tokens (set via Site Styles + Adobe Fonts kit).
   */

  .caa-sb54-landing {
    max-width: 56rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1.25rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__hero {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
    /* TEMP — see card rule below for context. Restore the hsla() rule
     * once Squarespace tokens resolve. */
    border-bottom: 3px solid rgb(33, 140, 165); /* TEMP */
    /* border-bottom: 3px solid hsla(var(--darkAccent-hsl), 1); */
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__eyebrow {
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    font-size: 0.875em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__lede {
    font-size: 1.125em;
    max-width: 40em;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__card {
    /* TEMP: hardcoded border color so the card renders with its border in
     * the local/GitHub-Pages preview. The intended rule below uses
     * --darkAccent-hsl, a Squarespace-injected token that only resolves
     * once the page is pasted into Squarespace. Without a visible border
     * the 2rem padding leaves the "Get Started" heading indented relative
     * to surrounding content. Remove this TEMP override (and restore the
     * commented hsla() rule) once Squarespace access lands and the page
     * renders against the site's design tokens. */
    border: 1px solid rgba(33, 140, 165, 0.18); /* TEMP — see comment above */
    /* border: 1px solid hsla(var(--darkAccent-hsl), 0.18); */
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__card > h2 {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__card > p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stages {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stage {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(13rem, max-content) 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: baseline;
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    /* TEMP — see card rule above for context. Restore the hsla() rule
     * once Squarespace tokens resolve. */
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(33, 140, 165, 0.18); /* TEMP */
    /* border-top: 1px solid hsla(var(--darkAccent-hsl), 0.18); */
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stage:first-child {
    border-top: none;
    padding-top: 0.25rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stage:last-child {
    padding-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stage-label {
    margin: 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 0.875em;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__stage-providers {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  @media (max-width: 540px) {
    .caa-sb54-landing__stage {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__note {
    padding: 1.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid hsla(var(--black-hsl), 0.1);
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__note > h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
  }

  .caa-sb54-landing__note > p {
    margin: 0;
  }
</style>
